headline: Traders Are Snapping Up Bullish Bets on Tesla
summary: Options traders are piling into bullish bets on Tesla after Elon Musk disclosed a $1 billion purchase of the EV-maker's stock. Some of the most actively-traded options contracts were Tesla call options that would pay out if shares jump to $430 or $450 apiece, according to Cboe Global Markets data.
